    <item>
      <title>Archaic Set</title>
      <author>Chalmoro Azohen</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/539090</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/539090#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">619f07daab4fd07587d7998e2419fd5a48f86268</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 23 Dec 2024 16:43:12 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66d2bd597616a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66d2bd6762967.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66d2bd676b703.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66d41200ce554.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; So THAT'S What Was Wrong&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;No actual file update quite yet, I'm afraid, but I'm pleased to announce that I've &lt;em&gt;finally&lt;/em&gt; fixed the bug on the Archaic Warm Greaves! See, the dye texture animations are... inconvenient... to edit, and it was reading the Archaic Legwear's textures instead, but that has now been fixed, I've tested it, all is well. I'm actually moving the chests where the armor is found and redoing a lot of stuff, so keep an eye out for the actual update!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;From &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/471343"&gt;KB0MB's Tears of the Kingdom mod&lt;/a&gt;, I present the Archaic Tunic, Legwear, and Warm Greaves from Tears of the Kingdom!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I've made a few edits, however.&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;I changed their locations. They're placed in spots reminiscent of their native game: the Archaic Legwear is &lt;span class="Spoiler SelectedElement"&gt;in the Shrine of Resurrection (compared to their position in the Cave of Awakening)&lt;/span&gt;, the Archaic Tunic is &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;by the Ja Baij Shrine (by the combat-related power Shrine, like its position close to the Fuse Shrine)&lt;/span&gt;, and the Archaic Warm Greaves are &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;behind the Mount Hylia waterfall&lt;/span&gt;. I've spoilered the locations for anyone who wants to find them without hints, but feel free to check if you just want to find them easily.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Rauru's arm is built into the Archaic Tunic, something that isn't the case in the original game and KB0MB's mod. Perfect for those who only want it with these. If people ask in the comments to have an option without the Rauru arm (ie. with Link's original arm), I suppose I can do that.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The last significant change I made is that there's an option in the BNP for whether you want to stay true to &lt;i&gt;Tears of the Kingdom&lt;/i&gt; and not upgrade the Archaic Set, or if you want to be able to upgrade it.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Oh, and note that long hair is not included. Sorry 'bout that. Other mods exist for that, though, no need to reinvent the wheel.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Many thanks to KB0MB for teaching me how to merge the arm on and allowing me to post this.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If there's any issues, just let me know in the comments and I'll take a look.</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/archaic_set_b4c23.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/archaic_set_26ab8.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Armor</category>
      <category>Skins</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Fixed ears in any headgear</title>
      <author>i2m</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/344894</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/344894#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">91452b6f507465c18fad2061275871da34d3bb4e</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Dec 2024 23:11:19 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/61c27d6540d31.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/61c27d753fda1.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/61c3a895c60eb.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/61c27d810db36.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Second Wind patch&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;Very small update:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Added a new BNP for users of the &lt;strong&gt;Second Wind mod&lt;/strong&gt;, in case they're getting ear bouncing with some of the headgear from that mod (only WiiU).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please note this patch is offered "as is", becase I'm not using Second Wind (but the solution to fix that problem is the same: editing the sbactorpack files as explained in the page).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Also, unified all the source ZIP files in a single one.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;DESCRIPTION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;This little mod will &lt;b&gt;lock the ear position in all the headgear&lt;/b&gt; that is allowing it, no matter what player replacement or mod are you using (Linkle, Zelda, default Link...).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Install it in case you are getting an endless bouncing ear movement in some headgear after installing mods like the &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/49763"&gt;Girly Animation Pack&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_earsf.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b class="SelectedElement"&gt;Ko-Fi:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://ko-fi.com/i2mods" target="_blank"&gt;https://ko-fi.com/i2mods&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;You can&amp;nbsp;support my works by buying me a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;a href="https://ko-fi.com/i2mods" target="_blank"&gt;coffee&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;:)&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;SETUP&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;Install the mod using the &lt;u&gt;latest BCML version&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;and make sure it's &lt;u&gt;at the absolute top&lt;/u&gt; (the highest priority in the mod load order).&amp;nbsp;During the install, you will be asked to apply the lock in all the listed headgear, or just in the ones you want to fix (the headgear not listed there, is safe and cannot be affected by the bouncing ear issue):&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/61c27d753fda1.jpg" width="60%"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;WARNINGS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This mod does &lt;u&gt;not cover new armors added to the game&lt;/u&gt; (but usually, all the new armors have this vector already at zero, so probably you will not get the bouncing ear issue on them).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Also, some &lt;u&gt;headgear is not upgradeable in the game&lt;/u&gt;: If you are using mods to allow it, this mod may not work correctly or it will only fix the bouncing ears issue in the not upgraded headgear.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;In general&lt;/u&gt;: if you have a mod containing&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;sbactorkpack &lt;/i&gt;files not listed in the Technical Stuff section below, and these files have the EarRotate vector with a non zero value, then you might get the bouncing ear issue for the headgear on that specific mod.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;THANKS!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;A big thanks to&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/members/2050277"&gt;bob920717&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;for discovering the solution, kindly sharing it with me, and also providing the &lt;u&gt;Switch&lt;/u&gt; version of the mod! Also thanks to&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1721593"&gt;OrionKaelin&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;who noticed the issue and helped trying several solutions, and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1675552"&gt;Liberator_Elite&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/2014011"&gt;rez11&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and other users who shared the issue in the comments of the Girly Animation Pack mod page and here :)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;TECHNICAL STUFF&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;Installed with BCML, the mod will change &lt;u&gt;only the value&lt;/u&gt; for the&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;EarRotate &lt;/b&gt;vector to (&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;0, 0, 0&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) in all the&amp;nbsp; existing&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;Armor_nnn_Head...&lt;b&gt;.&lt;/b&gt;sbactorpack&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;files in the game with this vector having a different value than zero (&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;67 files&lt;/span&gt; out of &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;186 in total&lt;/span&gt;, covering all the headgear present in the game + updates + DLC):&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/61c3a895c60eb.jpg"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/61c27d810db36.jpg" width="100%"&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/fixed_ears_any_headgear_wiiu.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/fixed_ears_any_headgear_switch.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/fixed_ears_second_wind_wiiu.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/fixed_ears_sources.zip" type="application/zip"/>
