      <guid isPermaLink="false">5bdcc3ff33332aead16226a5d1b554c749b22166</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 30 Nov 2024 19:35:45 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/641668a1ab1c5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/641668b2b17ab.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/641668bbf3fdb.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/641669b5e24e8.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/641e48fba7220.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/674b6a0b30c90.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/674b6a0c51a3d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/674b6a0cf3fb1.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/674b6a0d8643e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Second Wind v1.9.14 Update&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Amendment&lt;/em&gt;: Fixed infamous Cosy Set "claw hand" bug, or issues with it not loading at all&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Improvement&lt;/em&gt;: Updated dialogue to account for new additions to Second Wind&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Created Linkle versions of new outfits added in the update&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Adjustment&lt;/em&gt;: Changed Postman Hat model slightly&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Linkle - Second Wind Unofficial Patch&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;br&gt;I have no affiliation with the Linkle or Second Wind dev teams.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod provides cosmetic compatibility for Linkle and Second Wind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;What this means:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Fixed physics on all armours made upgradeable by Second Wind (Gerudo, Tingle, Royal Guard, Phantom/Ganon, etc.)&lt;br&gt;Linkle versions of all (current) Second Wind outfits.&lt;br&gt;Updated dialogue to refer to Linkle and use correct pronouns/titles.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;What this does NOT mean:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;del class="SelectedElement"&gt;This mod does not fix crashes when using Linkle 3.0 and entering shrines/Second Wind interiors.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/del&gt;Thanks to Second Wind's team, crashes are no longer an issue with Linkle 3.0!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;All Second Wind items have been covered. Linkle's hair will now appear on all headgear items, and the Cozy set's model has been replaced by the Radiant set (only without the illumination). There is optional Logical Braids support. Any future items added by Second Wind will eventually be covered by this mod. I have not made icons, but I implore anyone to make them if they so choose.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img data-cfsrc="https://i.imgur.com/n4rKgZ9.png" src="https://i.imgur.com/n4rKgZ9.png"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Logical Braids version&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Installation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Please make sure this mod has HIGHER priority than both Linkle 3.0 and Second Wind. All items seem to be working well for me, but let me know if you run into problems or compatibility issues. &lt;u&gt;Do not&lt;/u&gt; create a thread in Second Wind's discord server. I'm not part of the Second Wind team and they had no involvement in the creation of this mod besides granting me permission to do so. Any issues should be directed to me through GameBanana first. Failing that, my discord account is linked to my profile.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;Updated for SW 1.9.14 as of 30 November, 2024&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Patch notes are on the update page. Please completely uninstall any old version and install this version. Using "Update" on BCML can cause issues. I wanted to push this update out sooner than later so I haven't been able to add armour icons yet. While I do intend to do this, it is a tedious and lengthy task. Going into December, it's hard to say whether I will have the icons updated by the end of the year. If someone else is interested in creating icons, please feel free to do so.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;Dialogue Footnote&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;While I understand some dialogue mods for Linkle change the Gorons' use of "brother" and "bro" to "sister" and "sis", I do not intend to make these changes for this patch. I feel usage of those words, in the context of Gorons, is a stylistic and gender-neutral choice. Altering this, in my opinion, would neuter one of the distinct traits the Gorons have held since their inception.&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/linkle-secondwindunofficialpatch104.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/linkle-secondwindunofficialpatchv103.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/linkle-secondwindunofficialpatchv102.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
